                  <persName id="t18320405-258-person2193">
                  CHARLES 
                  HORATIO AUGUSTUS KIRBY
               <interp inst="t18320405-258-person2193" type="surname" value="HORATIO AUGUSTUS KIRBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-258-person2193" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-258-person2193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 3rd of January the prisoner came to Mr. William Blackburn's, where I was shopman; she offered a pair of trousers in pawn, which I agreed to take for 8s. - she asked me to let her do them up herself; I did, and instead of giving me the trousers, she gave me these old breeches, not worth a farthing, pinned up in this wrapper, and I gave her the 8s. on them - I should not have given it her without I had supposed I had the trousers, which were worth the money I agreed to lend.</p>
               <p>
            
